  "text": "Weight loss is common in cancer patients, and this could be attributed to diminished dietary intake as well as increased energy expenditure mediated by metabolic alterations caused by the tumor [CITATION_1] . Approximately 80% of patients with upper gastrointestinal cancers have substantial weight loss [CITATION_2] .",
